{"article_id":"DGlgrHlj56Vk7Wbh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"With attempts","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to attack Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh ' s record","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"failing ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Democrats over the weekend mounted a last-ditch bid","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"to derail his confirmation to the Supreme Court","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"by claiming","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that the vetting process is so bad","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that it demands a do-over .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Charles E. Schumer , New York Democrat , even accused former President George W. Bush of complicity ,","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"he used his powers","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"to block access to tens of thousands of pages of records from Judge Kavanaugh ' s time in the Bush White House .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Republicans brushed aside the complaints","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"and prepared to welcome Judge Kavanaugh to Capitol Hill on Tuesday for his appearance before the Senate Judiciary Committee ,","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"where the fate of his nomination will be decided .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , South Carolina Republican , said","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"as long as Judge Kavanaugh doesn ' t bungle the hearings ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"he will be confirmed","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"with some Democrats joining Republicans .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"\" If he does well at the hearing ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"he will get","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"- my belief -","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"55 [ votes ] .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Or higher","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"if he does well ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and I ' m sure","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"he will do well , \"","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Graham said on \" Fox News Sunday . \"","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"Democrats seemed to realize","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"they are fighting a losing battle","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"after attacks on the judge ' s personal finances and his activities while in the Bush White House fell short .","depth":4},{"id":31,"text":"Sen. Amy Klobuchar , Minnesota Democrat , expressed remorse","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"that her party eviscerated the power of the filibuster five years ago ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"leaving them no path","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"to stop Judge Kavanaugh ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"barring Republican defections .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Ms. Klobuchar ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"who voted with fellow Democrats in 2013","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to trigger the \" nuclear option \"","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"and curtail the filibuster ,","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"she would support reverting to the 60-vote rule","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"should her party regain the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"we should have made that change","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"when we look back at it .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"But it happened","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"because we were so frustrated","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"because President Obama wasn ' t able to get his nominees ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"but I think","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"we would have been in a better place now , \"","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"she said on NBC ' s \" Meet the Press . \"","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"She was one of several Democrats","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"who lodged complaints over the weekend","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"that Mr. Bush and President Trump were keeping damning documents from Judge Kavanaugh ' s past secret .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Nearly 450,000 pages of records have been turned over so far to the Judiciary Committee","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"- equivalent to the total for the past five high court nominees combined -","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"yet Democrats say","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Mr. Bush and Mr. Trump have deemed more than 100,000 pages \" committee confidential . \"","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"\" What are they trying so desperately to hide ? \"","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Mr. Schumer said .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"No land mines have been found in the hundreds of thousands of pages","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"already available to the public ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"and Republicans said","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"they have made the confidential documents available to all senators .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Sen. Charles E. Grassley , Iowa Republican and Judiciary Committee chairman , said","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"he would work with any senator","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"who requests","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"that some of those confidential documents be cleared for the public .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"Ms. Klobuchar was the only senator","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"to make such a request ,","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"he said -","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"and those documents were released Friday .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"They showed a fascinating conversation in March 2002 between Judge Kavanaugh , at the time a White House lawyer , and colleagues about the constitutionality of campaign finance laws","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"as Congress was debating a bill","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"pushed by Sens . John McCain and Russell D. Feingold .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"The judge was deeply skeptical of Congress ' ability","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"to impose restrictions ,","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"calling limits on outside groups \" blatantly unconstitutional \"","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"- a position","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"the Supreme Court eventually took as well","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"when it struck down the restrictions .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"He also said","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"that limits on contributions to candidates \" have some constitutional problems . \"","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"That stance is likely to anger Senate Democrats","depth":4},{"id":85,"text":"who want more campaign finance restrictions ,","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"arguing","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"that rich donors have gained too much influence in politics through their ability","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"to fund outside groups","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that run ads","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"influencing elections .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"In the emails , Judge Kavanaugh is debating Helgard C. Walker , another lawyer in the White House ,","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"with Noel Francisco also included in the conversation .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"Mr. Francisco is currently the solicitor general for the Justice Department ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"and Ms. Walker is a lawyer in private practice .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Ms. Walker and Judge Kavanaugh appeared to think","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"restrictions ran afoul of the Constitution ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"though they got into an intense email discussion over the role","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"outside groups play in campaigns .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Judge Kavanaugh said","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"issue ads from organizations such as the Chamber of Commerce or the Sierra Club can overwhelm the candidates ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"and the candidates are at a disadvantage","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"if they have to abide by limits","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"while the groups don ' t .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"\" I agree","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"that the issue ad restrictions are blatantly unconstitutional","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"although I think","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"the policy goal","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"of allowing the candidates to debate each other without background noise","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"that overwhelms the candidates/campaigns themselves","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"is quite laudable","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"( albeit unconstitutional ) , \"","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"he wrote .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"Ms. Walker said","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Judge Kavanaugh was demeaning outside groups","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"by calling their voices \" background noise . \"","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"Judge Kavanaugh said","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"he wasn ' t trying to insult those voices","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"but did fear","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"that they could be too loud","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"for the campaigns to break through .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"\" I do not like a political campaign","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"that is Sierra Club against Chamber of Commerce","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"with the candidates","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"reduced to bit roles","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"because of contribution limits , \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"The McCain-Feingold legislation ,","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"which Mr. Bush eventually signed into law ,","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"imposed strict limits","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"on how political parties could raise and spend money ,","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"and tried to limit the ability of outside groups","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"to weigh in with ads during the days ahead of the elections .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"The Supreme Court upheld most of the law in a 2003 case ,","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"but seven years later , in the Citizens United case , it ruled","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"that the restrictions on outside groups were unconstitutional","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"- just as Judge Kavanaugh predicted .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"That left a situation","depth":4},{"id":139,"text":"where parties are still heavily restricted ,","depth":5},{"id":140,"text":"but conservative and liberal groups are","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"not","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"- and they have become an overwhelming force in campaigns ,","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"also as Judge Kavanaugh predicted .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":287,"left":216,"right":286,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":171,"right":215,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":155,"right":170,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":146,"right":150,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":147,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":5,"right":148,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":8,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":9,"right":152,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":157,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":12,"right":156,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":160,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":15,"right":159,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":16,"right":158,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":158,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":167,"right":27,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"lef